article.headline: Late run, good defense hand No. 16 Vandy win
article.linkText: Late run, good defense hand No. 16 Vandy win
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA -- Hannah Tuomi scored 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds, and Vanderbilt (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) pulled away midway through the second half for a 59-46 victory over Saint Josephs on Tuesday night.

Jence Rhoads added 11 points and Jordan Coleman had a career-high 10 rebounds for the Commodores (4-0).

Ashley Logue had 12 points and 10 rebounds while Michelle Baker contributed a career-high 10 rebounds for the Hawks (1-3), who committed 20 turnovers and shot just 26 percent (16-for-61) from the field.

Despite the poor shooting, the Hawks only trailed 41-39 with 9:03 remaining. Vanderbilt then went on a 10-0 run over the next 6 minutes to put the game away. Coleman scored four points during the spurt.

Saint Josephs never got closer than 10 the rest of the game. The Hawks have not defeated a ranked team since a 71-69 victory over No. 15 Auburn on Dec. 29, 2007.
